div.p:
—we can provide no assurance that if American unions should take action against
                    shipping destined for the USSR, the
                    Administration will use its influence to prevent such actions;

—we will not refrain from employing diplomatic and other means, especially among
                    third world states, to embarrass the USSR with
                    respect to its actions in Angola;

—Secretary Kissinger’s proposed visit to
                    Moscow will proceed as a working visit in the common interest but without
                    ceremony;
